Struggle with depression mixed with anxiety, have been clean from self harm for years now and try really hard not to fall back on that way of coping
I have the most supportive girlfriend who sees me as me and the best younger sibling who is a great support as well
Having them and seeing people like you definitely give me hope that things will get better one day 💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙

Just wanted to stop by and tell you how awesome u are and how lucky young TransMen and TransWomen are to have you. I’m a cis female who doesn’t know you (of course) but I just watched some of your YouTube videos and I feel like super proud of you!! I’m so happy that you’re happy and helping so many other people along their journey who need you!! Keep it up! ☮️

At least 50% of TransMen attempt suicide at least once in their lives.
My first thought: But that doesn’t count the ones that actually succeeded.
•
This truth isn’t exactly something shocking to me-
I talk with TranMen all the time who are battling self hate, depression, thoughts of suicide.
I was a TransMan who suffered from suicidal thoughts as young as 12 years old-
I don’t talk in depth about my past battles with depression, self harm and other negative thoughts or feelings.
•
I’m sorry- because I don’t want to add to the illusion that anything is wrong with you if you are sad.
I really just want you to know that if I can do it- so can you.
We all have our own journey and I cannot tell you which is the best for you-
But I can say to surround yourself with positive people and BEING A MAN means owning up to your feelings and asking your Brotherhood for help
•
Let’s break the stigma-
If you or someone you know is suffering from depression and suicidal thoughts or self harm actions
Drop a 💙 to show your support
•
•
•
•
#transmen #men #transmenaremen #transmale #transgender #trans #masculinity #mascofcenter #depression #suicide #selfharm #aydiandowling #radicaloptimism #masc #manenough #manup

10 trans women of color have been killed or reported dead in 2019, half of them in June (PRIDE MONTH) and you’re opening a discussion about suicidal trans men? It’s obvious there’s a trans men “clique” on IG. You guys all follow each other and stick together but what about your trans sister’s who are being hunted down and murdered right now? Is that conversation not important enough to start on your IG? Is it not important to teach your trans brothers (WHO YOU EDUCATE SO WELL) to use their platforms to protect and bring awareness to their sisters in a dire time of need? Aydian I’m a little disappointed in you. smh Pink Mantaray has been using his platform to bring awareness to these murders of trans women all month. It’s not that hard to start a discussion about how the trans community needs to band together right now as a whole. You start discussions all the time. 🙄
💙 for myself and 💙 for everyone else also struggling. We've come this far, we can keep going, we just need to reach out to each other 💪

You were a huge inspiration to me when it came to beginning to transition and coming out in order to live as my authentic self, and you will always be such a huge inspiration as I continue bettering myself. Thank you 💙
Could you link the source to this? I am in nursing school and am writing an essay about transgender Health. Could use that!
reason number 621929487 why we don’t need straight pride
I'm trans and it's me 💙
@fightinghomophobicsteriotypes you are precious, with or without those scars. You are worthy and important. You are enough! 💙
@xristibaal thank you this made me cry 💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙
I have scars all up my arms from cutting because y family is transphobic and I’m not out yet💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙

💙💙 I am trying to let the people who support me be enough and when the thoughts invade and I start agreeing I feel like I don't love my support as much as I say which makes the depression so much worse. I'm trying really hard to be positive. I don't know what to do.
Ooh it’s true 💔

When I was young before even knowing what suicide was I wanted to just end and somehow literally be someone else or reincarnate or something into a boy.

Finally after having begun my social medical transition I for the first time in my life actually want to be myself! Not wishing i was another person.

but that doesnt mean i dont still struggle with depression and anxiety... Between still having dysphoria, and dealing with the social consequences of transitioning and discrimination my mental health still suffers from all that. 
but at least now i feel even a little better able to face it all because im actually starting to love myself.
💙 thank you for sharing this part of you
